OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783648071
OL,3,CJune heatwave keeps shoppers away from
OL,4,Cthe high street in blow to retailers
OL,6,F"Government action on business rates
OL,7,Fand energy costs would help unlock
OL,8,Finvestment to revive our local
OL,9,Fcommunities."
OL,11,FAndy Sumpter, a retail consultant for
OL,12,FSensormatic, said: "June saw UK retail
OL,13,Ffootfall remain under pressure, with
OL,14,Ftotal visits down 3.4% year-on-year,
OL,15,Fbringing the year-to-date figure down
OL,16,Fto minus 3.3% at the halfway point.
OL,18,F"While the overall trend remains
OL,19,Fsubdued, it continues to reflect a
OL,20,Fcautious consumer who is making fewer,
OL,21,Fmore considered trips.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@MO]tD@TOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
